@yungn - We do not have any alliance with geek squad.  As the only group that has ever cracked MRI, we have clearly been a thorn in their side.

@camster98 - Companies have been sued for using MRI.  If you use it from your IP once will you get sued - of course not.  You are correct that they do not call in and give IPs when they are running MRI at a client site.  The thing you are forgetting about is that if you continue to use MRI over and over from a single IP then their logging server will show an "unusual" amount of MRI use from your IP.  I don't know what the magic number is, but at some point they do take legal action to recoup losses.  So will you be sued if you use it to fix a few computers around the house - not likely.  Will you be sued if you use it to run a computer repair business - of course!

Contact MRI@GeekSquad.com for questions. :-P
